Now, I imagine this can just be easily solved by saying I need more AA and yeah, that is probably the problem, but I felt like I should ask anyways.<br>
<br>
I am level 63 and I have 3839 HP with almost FULL HP gear, some of it being 60-100 hp's and only one NO DROP item. Everyone, well - most people tell me that sucks! I just don't get it, and it's really frustrating to be a warrior with such low HP's (although they could be high? Who knows ...) Now besides needing to get into an uber guild, why are my HP's so low? Clerics bitch and moan about my HP being low, is it simply because I don't have the AA? I talked to a few warriors &amp; they say they have 4100-4200 HP (and not nearly as good HP gear as I have) ... at level 61. I have low stam, so I know that is also a problem but I really can't figure it out ... how can someone be raid buffed 7k+ whereas with full cler/sham buffs I push low 6k, now this same person has 5300 HP unbuffed. I don't see myself gaining 1500 hp from aa alone!<br>
<br>
I probably in all reality should of exp-grinded 30-50 AA before moving up in levels so fast, it's gonna be hard to get 100+ aa at 65 &amp; I don't even know if I can take the levelling thing anymore, it gets old without a good guild &amp; dying 12 times in 6 hours because your clerics CH 120-1k HP in PoS.<br>
